      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOUTHERN MONARCH (2) is a lightly raced mare who is a winner of two of three so far and has good early speed. Aided by the claim and expected to take running down again. PETIT EAGLE (7) is close to a win, finishing fourth two back then placed here in a similar race last time when beaten less than a length. Sure to be in the finish. LOCA BELLA (9) doesn't win out of turn with just the maiden success from 20 starts but placed 2/3 here and placed only try this course and distance. Overdue and will be tough to hold out. MAGNA TORINO (6) wound up strongly to score the maiden win last time over 1200m. Drawn for a soft run and aided by the claim. Looks a leading chance again. I'M KENNY (4) was beaten three lengths in a tougher assignment last time. Well placed here and should be in this for a long way.",
